# Multi-platform portability (Windows + macOS + Linux).
# Normalise ALL text files to LF in the working tree on every OS, regardless of each
# developer's local `core.autocrlf`. This stops CRLF from sneaking in and breaking
# byte-sensitive files such as the hash-chained audit log + checkpoint (the \r\n bug
# we already hit). LF is the single canonical line ending for this submission.
* text=auto eol=lf
